HEADWORD: Guhr
<hw>Guhr</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[G.]</ety> <def>A loose,
earthy deposit from water, found in the cavities or clefts of rocks,
mostly white, but sometimes red or yellow, from a mixture of clay or
ocher.</def> <rj><au>P. Cleaveland.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Guiac</ent>⟦br⟧
